com.pwn9.filter.engine.rules.chain

Class RuleChain

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pwn9.filter.engine.rules.chain.RuleChain
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Chain, ChainEntry

    public class RuleChain
extends Object
implements Chain, ChainEntry
    The RuleChain contains a compiled version of all the rules in the text file. A RuleChain is a chain of Rules. The high-level process is:

    Load a chain of rules from a text file, parse them into a chain The Event Handler calls the RuleChain.apply() method with the FilterContext The apply() method iterates over the rules one at a time; matching, checking conditions, and executing actions based on the message and the rules.

      • apply

        public void apply(FilterContext context,
                  FilterService filterService)
           throws IllegalStateException
        Iterate over the chain in order, checking the Rule pattern against the current message. If the text pattern matches, test the rule conditions, to ensure they are all met. If all of the conditions are met, execute the Rule's actions in sequential order. If the Rule sets the stop=true of the FilterTask, stop processing rules. If not, continue along the rule chain, checking the (possibly modified) message against subsequent rules.
        Specified by:
        apply in interface ChainEntry
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException
